    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Portuguese tester beds with turned elements and carvings on the headboard; generally having turned posts and either a plain or pagoda-shaped tester. Of a type made in the 16th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
